latestPosts.caption:
Krupya maaf kare - Bada$$ery mere DNA mein hai! ✨

Also, I think I cleaned up well. What do you think?

[40s fashion, GRWM as a 40yr old, 40+ skincare, dating in 40s, life in 40s, 40+ dating]

I thought I’ll be married by 30 to the love of my life and have children of my own. But life as we know it, had other plans. I only went from one toxic relationship to another getting my self-worth depleted, while I sat over a pile of broken dreams. 

After giving into the dependency of having a partner constantly, I finally chose to be single and do the work. It’s been 5 years of healing, thriving and growing.

I felt really lonely in some of my relationships, while I feel so complete now in my own company. Life is such an exceptional teacher if you let it.

I started this page around the same time as when my last relationship was ending, not knowing what I was doing. And while people may think of social media as largely insignificant in their lives, this page has been my means to finding myself all over again. 

While I felt deeply disrespected in the relationships I chose, this page has helped me gain the love and respect amongst my audience and peers through my work. Helping me regain my sense of self-worth and confidence. 

Funny back story, I contemplated for a whole year before starting this page because thanks to my low sense of self-worth, I thought no one really wanted to hear anything from me. Turns out I was wrong.

People around me sometimes think I have very high standards for someone in her 40s seeking a partnership. But after doing all the work there’s no way I’m settling for anything less than what I deserve. It doesn’t matter what age I am at, because I take great pride in growing older as I’ve realised this is my best version yet and it gets better each day.

How quick is quick? Got you!
Tell me will you try this? 

[valentine date look, Valentines Day, vday look, GRWM in 5 min, quick and easy makeup looks, easy every day makeup look, easy makeup tutorial, every day makeup inspiration]

Full review 👇

💋 The formula is buttery and offers a really comfortable glide

💋They offer a beautiful pigment pay off that is buildable. Each colour is beautiful and quite brown skin friendly. 

💋 There is a coconut-ey fragrance that is pleasant and mild. 

💋 These are true glosses, offering high shine that stays for a while. And much like any other gloss, they do transfer. These don’t offer any stain - However, the deepest shade of red does leave behind a faint tone on the lips. 

💋 The formula is thick and can be a bit goopy leading to stringiness, but nothing that can’t be worked around. 

💋 Packaging is an area the brand really needs to work on - The concept is cute and the applicator is nice at the price point. However, the caps don’t close well or fit perfectly. 

P.S: The products were sent in PR by the brand with no obligation to post.
